{"title_page": "Gulberg Town, Karachi", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Gulberg (Lahore)}}\n{{unreferenced|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->| name                            = Gulberg Town\n| native_name                     = <br/>{{nq|\u06af\u0644\u0628\u0631\u06af \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646\u200e}}\n| settlement_type                 = [[Towns in Karachi|Constituent Town of Karachi]]\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->| image_skyline                   = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| image_seal                      = \n| image_map                       = GulbergTown Karachi.PNG\n| map_caption                     = Gulberg Town was divided into 8 Union Councils\n<!-- Location ------------------>| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1               = Province\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sindh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = City District\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Karachi]]\n| parts_type                      = Union Councils\n| parts_style                     = coll, para\n| parts                           = 8\n| p1                              = [[Ayesha Manzil]]<br>[[Ancholi]]<br>[[Azizabad (Karachi)|Azizabad]]<br>[[Karimabad (Karachi)|Karimabad]]<br>[[Shafiq Mill Colony]]<br>[[Naseerabad (Karachi)|Naseerabad]]<br>[[Water Pump]]<br>[[Yaseenabad]]\n\n<!-- Politics ----------------->| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = Town Council\n| leader_title                    = Town Nazim\n| leader_name                     = Mohammad Kamal Malik\n| leader_title1                   = Naib Nazim\n| leader_name1                    = Saeed Ahmed Sidiqi\n| leader_title2                   = Municipal Officer\n| leader_name2                    = Latif Lodhi\n| established_title               = Established\n| established_date                = 14 August 2001\n<!-- Area    --------------------->| area_magnitude                  = 1 E+6\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_total_sq_mi                = <!-- Elevation -------------------------->\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = <!-- Population   ----------------------->\n| population_as_of                = 1998\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 453490\n<!-- General information  --------------->| timezone                        = \n| utc_offset                      = \n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| latd                            = \n| latm                            = \n| lats                            = \n| latNS                           = \n| longd                           = \n| longm                           = \n| longs                           = \n| longEW                          = <!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n| postal_code_type                = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| website                         = \n| official_name                   = \n| extinct_title                   = Disbanded\n| extinct_date                    = 2011\n}}\n\n'''Gulberg Town'''  ([[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] and {{lang-ur|{{nq|\u06af\u0644\u0628\u0631\u06af}}}}) was a [[Towns in Karachi|Karachi borough]] in the northern  part of the city. Gulberg Town was formed in 2001 as part of [https://web.archive.org/web/20081013065059/http://www.nrb.gov.pk/city_district/index.html The Local Government Ordinance 2001], and was subdivided into 11 [[Union councils of Pakistan|union councils]]. The town system was disbanded in 2011,<ref>{{Cite book|last=Gayer|first=Laurent|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BklRBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA156&lpg=PA156&dq=karachi+towns+disbanded+2011&source=bl&ots=a0EX8EYYqr&sig=ACfU3U1ZiUfKRKtF9CzZQ7yMEaA8aAfgPg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwir4qiZ--3oAhXjK30KHRWgDCsQ6AEwAnoECA8QKA#v=onepage&q=karachi%20towns%20disbanded%202011&f=false|title=Karachi: Ordered Disorder and the Struggle for the City|date=2014|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-935444-3|language=en}}</ref> and Gulberg Town was re-organized as part of [[Karachi Central|Karachi Central District]] in 2015.\n\n== Location ==\nGulberg Town was bordered by the [[Lyari River]] and [[Gulshan Town]] to the east and the [[Gujjar Nala]] stream and [[North Nazimabad Town]] to the west. Also neighbouring Gulberg were [[New Karachi Town|New Karachi]] and [[Gadap Town|Gadap]] to the north and [[Liaquatabad Town|Liaquatabad]] to the south.\n\n== History ==\nThe federal government under [[Pervez Musharraf]], who seized power in a [[1999 Pakistani coup d'\u00e9tat|1999 coup d'etat]], introduced local government reforms in the year 2000, which eliminated the previous \"third tier of government\" ([[Divisions of Pakistan|administrative divisions]]) and replaced it with the fourth tier ([[Districts of Pakistan|districts]]). The effect in Karachi was the dissolution of the former [[Karachi Division]] in 2001, and the merging of its five districts to form a new Karachi City-District with eighteen autonomous constituent towns including Gulberg Town. In 2011, the system was disbanded but remained in place for bureaucratic administration until 2015, when the [[Karachi Metropolitan Corporation]] system was reintroduced. In 2015, Gulberg Town was re-organized as part of [[District of Central Karachi|Karachi Central]] district.\n\n== Education and academia ==\nApart from the socio-economic diversification, this town had the distinction of being one of the most literate middle/upper middle class parts of the city along with [[North Nazimabad Town]]. There were numerous coaching centres in Gulberg Town, among them C.A.M.P. Collegiate is one of the famous coaching centre which is located in Block 10, Federal.B.Area.\n\n\"Markaz-e-Umeed\" (The Hope Center) is one of the oldest schools for [[Intellectual disability|intellectually disabled]] children in Pakistan, established in 1971.\n\n== Hospitals ==\n* Tabba Center of Heart Diseases\n* Habib Medical Center\n* Aga Khan Hospital for Women Karimabad(Ayesha Manzil)\n* Usman Memorial Hospital\n* Mamjee Care Center\n* Aziza Husseni Hospital\n* Karachi Institute of Heart Diseases ( CDGK )\n* Federal Hospital\n* Alnoor Hospital\n* Muhammadi Hospital\n\n== Neighbourhoods ==\n* [[Samanabad (Karachi)|Samanabad]]\n* [[Aisha Manzil]]\n* [[Ancholi]]\n* [[Azizabad (Karachi)|Azizabad]]\n* [[Karimabad (Karachi)|Karimabad]]\n* [[Shafiq Mill Colony]]\n* [[Naseerabad (Karachi)|Naseerabad]]\n* [[Water Pump]]\n* [[Yaseenabad]]\n* [[Musa Colony]]\n* [[Dastagir Colony]]\n* [[Hussainabad (Karachi)|Hussainabad]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.kmc.gos.pk/Contents.aspx?id=84 Districts of Karachi]\n\n{{Karachi Towns}}\n{{Karachi topics}}\n\n{{Coord|24.9369|N|67.0759|E|type:city_region:PK|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Gulberg Town, Karachi| ]]\n\n\n{{Karachi-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Gulberg (Lahore)}}\n{{unreferenced|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->| name                            = Gulberg Town\n| native_name                     = <br/>{{nq|\u06af\u0644\u0628\u0631\u06af \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646\u200e}}\n| settlement_type                 = [[Towns in Karachi|Constituent Town of Karachi]]\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->| image_skyline                   = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| image_seal                      = \n| image_map                       = GulbergTown Karachi.PNG\n| map_caption                     = Gulberg Town was divided into 8 Union Councils\n<!-- Location ------------------>| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1               = Province\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sindh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = City District\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Karachi]]\n| parts_type                      = Union Councils\n| parts_style                     = coll, para\n| parts                           = 8\n| p1                              = [[Ayesha Manzil]]<br>[[Ancholi]]<br>[[Azizabad (Karachi)|Azizabad]]<br>[[Karimabad (Karachi)|Karimabad]]<br>[[Shafiq Mill Colony]]<br>[[Naseerabad (Karachi)|Naseerabad]]<br>[[Water Pump]]<br>[[Yaseenabad]]\n\n<!-- Politics ----------------->| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = Town Council\n| leader_title                    = Town Nazim\n| leader_name                     = Mohammad Kamal Malik\n| leader_title1                   = Naib Nazim\n| leader_name1                    = Saeed Ahmed Sidiqi\n| leader_title2                   = Municipal Officer\n| leader_name2                    = Latif Lodhi\n| established_title               = Established\n| established_date                = 14 August 2001\n<!-- Area    --------------------->| area_magnitude                  = 1 E+6\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_total_sq_mi                = <!-- Elevation -------------------------->\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = <!-- Population   ----------------------->\n| population_as_of                = 1998\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 453490\n<!-- General information  --------------->| timezone                        = \n| utc_offset          